main event: On August 26, 1966, two bright lights were observed in the sky near Carpio, North Dakota, which were stationary for about 15 minutes.
interesting points: The observer reported the lights as very bright and steady,The objects were about 15 to 20 degrees above the horizon,Another UFO was visually identified and confirmed via radar during the same timeframe,The lights were suspected to be caused by an aircraft but the observer found them unusual and unexplained,Physical evidence was noted despite there being no photographs taken.
sighted object: two bright lights in the sky
witness description: the observer believed the lights to be unusual and unexplained based on personal experience
